01:03:49.280 --> 01:03:54.520
This is very simple,
and it's solar powered.

01:03:54.520 --> 01:03:56.530
You put it out
eight hours a day,

01:03:56.530 --> 01:03:59.950
and it gives you eight
hours a night of light.

01:03:59.950 --> 01:04:04.840
Operation Blessing handed
out-- and through the Hispanic

01:04:04.840 --> 01:04:05.980
Federation--

01:04:05.980 --> 01:04:10.360
about half a million of these
all throughout Puerto Rico.

01:04:10.360 --> 01:04:12.100
This is my new American Express.

01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:13.570
I never leave home without it.

01:04:13.570 --> 01:04:15.380
[LAUGHTER]

01:04:15.380 --> 01:04:16.490
But the answer is yes.

01:04:16.490 --> 01:04:20.080
So if you have a
connection, just

01:04:20.080 --> 01:04:22.207
let him know we're waiting.

01:04:22.207 --> 01:04:24.790
- And I know I'm not supposed
to really ask a second question,

01:04:24.790 --> 01:04:27.070
but just really quick just
because I've been freaking out

01:04:27.070 --> 01:04:28.653
the whole week looking
forward to this

01:04:28.653 --> 01:04:30.220
and I'm sweating a little bit.

01:04:30.220 --> 01:04:32.450
I just wanted to know,
can I have a hug?

01:04:32.450 --> 01:04:32.950
- Yes.

01:04:32.950 --> 01:04:36.387
[LAUGHTER]

01:04:37.860 --> 01:04:41.297
[APPLAUSE]

01:04:59.970 --> 01:05:02.408
How old are you?

01:05:02.408 --> 01:05:03.780
- 24.

01:05:03.780 --> 01:05:06.840
- 24 and he's been freaking out.

01:05:06.840 --> 01:05:07.770
I'm 56.

01:05:07.770 --> 01:05:09.270
I know I don't look
it, but I'm 56.

01:05:12.570 --> 01:05:13.650
Oh, you could be my son.

01:05:13.650 --> 01:05:14.428
[LAUGHTER]

01:05:14.428 --> 01:05:16.220
- That's why I called you tia.

01:05:16.220 --> 01:05:18.360
- Oh.

01:05:18.360 --> 01:05:19.060
Hi.

01:05:19.060 --> 01:05:21.210
- Hi.

01:05:21.210 --> 01:05:22.530
It's a simple enough question.

01:05:22.530 --> 01:05:24.130
We have a room full of people.

01:05:24.130 --> 01:05:27.240
I'm-- sorry, I'm throwing
something your way--

01:05:27.240 --> 01:05:29.100
I'm assuming everyone
here has some

01:05:29.100 --> 01:05:32.700
resources, some friends, some
connections, some knowledge.

01:05:32.700 --> 01:05:34.950
What do you need most?

01:05:34.950 --> 01:05:37.410
You are still
dealing with stuff.

01:05:37.410 --> 01:05:41.040
I assume they haven't sent
you $91 million dollars.

01:05:41.040 --> 01:05:42.540
And what do you need most?

01:05:42.540 --> 01:05:43.860
- We need three things.

01:05:43.860 --> 01:05:47.520
- And after that, if you can
tell people where to look,

01:05:47.520 --> 01:05:49.680
if it's something
they can't provide,

01:05:49.680 --> 01:05:52.260
to find out what else you need.

01:05:52.260 --> 01:05:53.420
- Thank you, by the way.

01:05:56.740 --> 01:06:02.970
One of the things we need is
forms and platforms like this.

01:06:02.970 --> 01:06:08.090
And for you all to become
ambassadors of hope

01:06:08.090 --> 01:06:12.710
for Puerto Rico, and
frankly for any other area--

01:06:12.710 --> 01:06:16.040
Pine Ridge, the
young man mentioned--

01:06:16.040 --> 01:06:18.500
but we need for Puerto
Rico to continue

01:06:18.500 --> 01:06:22.060
to be part of the conversation.

01:06:22.060 --> 01:06:25.210
Not to be an asterisk at
the end of a paragraph,

01:06:25.210 --> 01:06:27.770
but to continue to be
part of the conversation.

01:06:27.770 --> 01:06:31.120
So anything you see about
Puerto Rico, retweet,

01:06:31.120 --> 01:06:33.190
share on Facebook, and so forth.

01:06:33.190 --> 01:06:33.940
That's number one.

01:06:33.940 --> 01:06:39.520
Number two is we really need
the money that was allocated

01:06:39.520 --> 01:06:40.850
to get to Puerto Rico.

01:06:40.850 --> 01:06:43.750
So call your Congresswoman
or your Congressman,

01:06:43.750 --> 01:06:48.520
call your Senator and
tell them, hey, what up?

01:06:48.520 --> 01:06:50.600
Give us-- send the money down.

01:06:50.600 --> 01:06:53.710
It's been allocated.

01:06:53.710 --> 01:06:59.350
It's just an issue of not using
this in a vindictive behavior.

01:06:59.350 --> 01:07:02.990
And number three, like the
young man before you said,

01:07:02.990 --> 01:07:09.800
we need to make sure that
in a dual way we have power.

01:07:09.800 --> 01:07:13.220
Power that will
give us the ability

01:07:13.220 --> 01:07:19.800
to have a strong and
forceful economy,

01:07:19.800 --> 01:07:23.670
but also the power to decide.

01:07:23.670 --> 01:07:26.520
So if you could do
one thing, think

01:07:26.520 --> 01:07:31.530
about Puerto Rico and
our right to decide

01:07:31.530 --> 01:07:34.200
what the next step in our
relationship with the United

01:07:34.200 --> 01:07:36.210
States is.

01:07:36.210 --> 01:07:41.220
And help us ensure that
all the voices are heard.

01:07:41.220 --> 01:07:43.830
I've said to you once
what I believe in.

01:07:43.830 --> 01:07:46.350
I'm not trying to convince
you of what I believe in.

01:07:46.350 --> 01:07:47.820
I'm trying to ask
you to help me.

01:07:47.820 --> 01:07:49.050
You know Jerry Maguire?

01:07:49.050 --> 01:07:50.550
Help me help you.

01:07:50.550 --> 01:07:58.480
Well, help me tell Congress that
all voices need to be heard.

01:07:58.480 --> 01:08:01.260
And never forget us.

01:08:01.260 --> 01:08:02.700
Never forget us.

01:08:02.700 --> 01:08:05.490
Never forget anyone
that's in need.

01:08:05.490 --> 01:08:08.550
And if you're here,
it's because you don't.

01:08:08.550 --> 01:08:11.720
You have something
innate in you,

01:08:11.720 --> 01:08:15.210
ingrained in your
psyche and your soul

01:08:15.210 --> 01:08:17.050
for people that for
whatever reason,

01:08:17.050 --> 01:08:20.040
have had to move from
one place to another.

01:08:20.040 --> 01:08:22.384
And that's important.

01:08:25.189 --> 01:08:26.370
Somebody help us.

01:08:26.370 --> 01:08:30.660
It's a foundation-- you can
give to many foundations.

01:08:30.660 --> 01:08:35.630
But I started getting Santa
Claus mail-- you know,

01:08:35.630 --> 01:08:38.590
tons of mail.

01:08:38.590 --> 01:08:43.340
A kid in Ohio send
me his $1 allowance.

01:08:43.340 --> 01:08:48.029
A teacher-- a retired teacher
from Houston send me $25.

01:08:48.029 --> 01:08:52.370
And all over the United States--
places that I have never heard

01:08:52.370 --> 01:08:54.080
and will probably never visit--

01:08:54.080 --> 01:08:56.479
people would say,
Mayor, this is for you.

01:08:56.479 --> 01:08:57.920
Do with it what you may.

01:08:57.920 --> 01:09:00.470
So we had to set up a structure.

01:09:00.470 --> 01:09:05.210
I think we've raised
about $600,000.

01:09:05.210 --> 01:09:09.319
We've already used part of
that, because the structure

01:09:09.319 --> 01:09:14.590
of a foundation allows us to
use 25% outside of San Juan.

01:09:14.590 --> 01:09:17.120
And now we're in the
midst of finalizing

01:09:17.120 --> 01:09:21.950
the selection of homes in
San Juan where people have

01:09:21.950 --> 01:09:30.560
bedridden relatives or children
with disabilities or functional

01:09:30.560 --> 01:09:34.069
diversities that need to
be hooked up to something,

01:09:34.069 --> 01:09:37.010
or powered in order to live.

01:09:37.010 --> 01:09:39.800
So we're going to
provide those homes,

01:09:39.800 --> 01:09:42.260
fully equip them
with solar power

01:09:42.260 --> 01:09:45.229
so that they can run their
homes completely, and not

01:09:45.229 --> 01:09:49.819
be at risk of losing their
lives just because a huff

01:09:49.819 --> 01:09:56.150
and puff comes and the
electricity just leaves.

01:09:56.150 --> 01:09:59.685
It's called SomebodyHelpUs.org
or [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]..

01:10:02.580 --> 01:10:03.330
Hi.

01:10:03.330 --> 01:10:03.830
- Hi.

01:10:03.830 --> 01:10:06.580
I'm Marisa Rodriguez Garcia.

01:10:06.580 --> 01:10:08.630
I'm a native of Vega Baja.

01:10:08.630 --> 01:10:09.840
- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

01:10:09.840 --> 01:10:14.710
- [NON ENGLISH SPEECH] And
a member of the diaspora.

01:10:14.710 --> 01:10:17.950
We felt a little bit of
the wind of Maria here,

01:10:17.950 --> 01:10:21.640
and that leads to two questions.

01:10:21.640 --> 01:10:25.540
One, is there anything you want
from the five million of us

01:10:25.540 --> 01:10:27.120
here?

01:10:27.120 --> 01:10:32.630
And number two, if we dream
of the future and something

01:10:32.630 --> 01:10:39.490
is finally coming our way
of your dream of real--

01:10:39.490 --> 01:10:43.120
- A process of
self-determination.

01:10:43.120 --> 01:10:47.560
- What will happen to the
five million of us here?

01:10:47.560 --> 01:10:49.595
Will you forget us?

01:10:49.595 --> 01:10:51.470
- Well, that's interesting
that you say that.

01:10:51.470 --> 01:10:54.470
And I have to tell
you that I think

01:10:54.470 --> 01:10:55.970
that one of the
things that happened

01:10:55.970 --> 01:10:59.630
is that there are
really no more you

01:10:59.630 --> 01:11:04.030
and us when it comes to the
Puerto Rican population.

01:11:04.030 --> 01:11:10.110
We're really one big
group divided by an ocean.

01:11:10.110 --> 01:11:16.210
Before, people in Puerto Rico
would say [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]..

01:11:16.210 --> 01:11:18.170
It was the diaspora
from Chicago that

01:11:18.170 --> 01:11:21.270
first took food to San Juan.

01:11:21.270 --> 01:11:23.810
It was the diaspora
through Hispanic Federation

01:11:23.810 --> 01:11:28.430
that gave us 270,000 pounds
of food that got there

01:11:28.430 --> 01:11:31.730
before FEMA's food got there.

01:11:31.730 --> 01:11:35.030
FEMA was giving us as food--

01:11:35.030 --> 01:11:37.460
and I remember watching
this box and saying,

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:40.910
oh, God, there's
an entree in here.

01:11:40.910 --> 01:11:43.790
And it was beef jerky.

01:11:43.790 --> 01:11:49.670
Beef jerky, apple sauce, a
Babe Ruth, chocolate pudding,

01:11:49.670 --> 01:11:52.670
and a little can of Pringles.

01:11:52.670 --> 01:11:53.630
That was food.

01:11:56.510 --> 01:11:59.560
That was food.

01:11:59.560 --> 01:12:01.390
And when some of
us complained, they

01:12:01.390 --> 01:12:04.729
said, if you're
hungry you eat it.

01:12:04.729 --> 01:12:05.715
Well, that's true.

01:12:08.680 --> 01:12:10.720
That's true.

01:12:10.720 --> 01:12:13.240
But if you're a diabetic
and you eat that, you die.

01:12:16.640 --> 01:12:20.180
So the diaspora--

01:12:20.180 --> 01:12:24.470
Philip Levine that was Mayor
of Miami Beach at the time--

01:12:24.470 --> 01:12:30.680
Houston, California,
Boston, Chicago, New York,

01:12:30.680 --> 01:12:32.165
held us together.

01:12:36.130 --> 01:12:39.970
So you cannot forget
what is part of you.

01:12:39.970 --> 01:12:45.130
And you're a part of us
and we are a part of you.

01:12:45.130 --> 01:12:51.780
We will forever be linked by a
horrible situation that helped

01:12:51.780 --> 01:12:54.030
us find our way to each other.

01:12:56.680 --> 01:13:01.420
The question is, what can we
do together moving forward?

01:13:01.420 --> 01:13:05.670
Jossie Valentin that's
here with me is--

01:13:05.670 --> 01:13:08.480
or I'm here with her--

01:13:08.480 --> 01:13:11.840
she's a Mount Holyoke
City Councilor.

01:13:11.840 --> 01:13:15.300
She's part of a diaspora.

01:13:15.300 --> 01:13:17.760
I personally believe
then whatever

01:13:17.760 --> 01:13:19.740
happens in Puerto
Rico, the diaspora

01:13:19.740 --> 01:13:22.770
should have a vote in it.

01:13:22.770 --> 01:13:24.270
But I have to tell
you that's not

01:13:24.270 --> 01:13:28.150
shared by a lot of
people in Puerto Rico.

01:13:28.150 --> 01:13:32.100
So no, I will never forget you
because you saved the lives

01:13:32.100 --> 01:13:34.650
of the people that I love.

01:13:34.650 --> 01:13:40.150
And I learned that
I was mistaken

01:13:40.150 --> 01:13:43.470
when I called you them.

01:13:43.470 --> 01:13:45.050
I should have always
called you us.

01:13:48.459 --> 01:13:51.868
[APPLAUSE]

01:13:56.760 --> 01:14:01.280
- For her citizenship and for
a wonderful moment of education

01:14:01.280 --> 01:14:03.740
for all of us, let me
thank Mayor Cruz again.

01:14:03.740 --> 01:14:04.490
Thank you so much.

01:14:04.490 --> 01:14:04.990
[APPLAUSE]

01:14:04.990 --> 01:14:08.140
